  "prompt": "Why did Quora limit question details to 300 words?",
  "response": "Quora likely limited question details to 300 words to encourage clarity, conciseness, and accessibility. Here are some possible reasons for this decision:\n\n1. **Improved Readability**: Shorter question details are easier to read and understand, making it more likely that users will engage with the question and provide meaningful answers.\n\n2. **Focus on Core Inquiry**: Limiting the word count encourages users to focus on the essence of their question, reducing the likelihood of overly verbose or tangential explanations.\n\n3. **Encourages Simplicity**: A shorter limit helps maintain a clean and simple interface, making the platform more user-friendly.\n\n4. **Streamlined Moderation**: Shorter question details are easier to moderate and review, helping to maintain quality and reduce the risk of spam or inappropriate content.\n\n5. **Consistency Across the Platform**: A word limit ensures uniformity in how questions are presented, creating a more consistent user experience.\n\n6. **Encourages Follow-Up in Answers**: If users need to provide additional context, they can do so in their answers or comments, fostering a more dynamic and interactive discussion.\n\nBy implementing this limit, Quora aims to balance user expression with the need for clear, effective communication on the platform.",
